# Everden Visual Verify (always)

Nick's rule: **look at it**. Green unit tests are not a screenshot.

Global rule: `.cursor/rules/visual-verify-when-building.mdc` (before/after proof table for Look / Outfits / Folk).

## Hard requirement

Before claiming creator, HUD, dialogue, combat UI, district, or title-screen work done:

1. `npm run dev` (or preview) on a known port
2. Browser MCP: walk the real path (not only `?qa=1` when validating player-facing UI)
3. Save screenshots under `docs/playtests/screenshots/`
4. Run Playwright for the touched flow (e.g. `npx playwright test e2e/character-creation.spec.ts`)
5. Append / update `docs/playtests/AGENT_RUNS.md` (AR-NNN) with what you saw and bugs fixed
6. Re-shot after every visual bugfix
7. **Before/after pairs** for Look (pattern, tint, markings) and Outfits (hat/cloak/accessory) — pixel change without visible screenshot diff = FAIL

## "Verified" means

| Claim | Required proof |
|-------|----------------|
| Menu / creator works | Live click all new tabs + enter game + screenshot Causeway/HUD |
| Save/settings toggle | Toggle in UI, confirm behavior (e.g. no narration panel), save if needed |
| Presentation / districts | `everden-visual-gate.mdc` G1–G5 + scout log |

Mechanical only (`npm test`) → write **"mechanical only — visual pending"** in the CHECKIN. Never imply eye-check done.

## Bugs found in AR-021 (do not regress)

- Folk change must update center title immediately (`render()`, not partial refresh)
- Panel re-draws must `renderPanel()` / clear — never append a second panel
- Story motivation guide note must refresh with selection

